## 2️⃣ Prochaine étape critique – **Rate‑limit & Secret Manager**

### 2.1 Rate‑limit (middleware)

Je vais ajouter un fichier `backend/src/common/interceptors/rate-limit.interceptor.ts` qui utilise `express-rate-limit` :

```ts
import { Injectable, NestInterceptor, CallHandler, ExecutionContext } from '@nestjs/common';
import rateLimit from 'express-rate-limit';

@Injectable()
export class RateLimitInterceptor implements NestInterceptor {
  private limiter = rateLimit({
    windowMs: 60_000,          // 1 min
    max: 5,                    // max 5 req/min per IP
    message: { error: 'Too many requests, please try again later.' },
    keyGenerator: (req) => req.ip,
  });

  intercept(context: ExecutionContext, next: CallHandler) {
    const req = context.switchToHttp().getRequest();
    const res = context.switchToHttp().getResponse();
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      this.limiter(req, res, (err) => (err ? reject(err) : resolve(next.handle())));
    });
  }
}
```

Ensuite, je l’appliquerai globalement dans `main.ts` :

```ts
app.useGlobalInterceptors(new RateLimitInterceptor());
```

